When the user asks to use "release" to do something, here is the help for the release cli. 

release --help
The official CLI for Release (release.com)

Usage:
  release [command]

Available Commands:
  accounts     Manage accounts
  ai           Work with ai
  apps         Manage apps
  auth         Manage authentication (login, logout, etc.)
  builds       Manage builds
  clusters     Manage clusters
  completion   Generate the autocompletion script for the specified shell
  datasets     Manage datasets
  deploys      Manage deploys
  development  Work with remote development environments
  environments Manage environments
  gitops       Manage GitOps config
  help         Help about any command
  instances    Manage instances

Flags:
      --config string   config file (default is $HOME/.release.yaml)
      --debug           enable debug logging
  -h, --help            help for release
  -v, --version         version for release

Use "release [command] --help" for more information about a command.